description:
Responsibilities

To Handle the public complaints, queries, requests, claims, attending neighborhood meetings & any other public concerned issues in connection with the project works;
Communicate and liaise with the local community and District Council members.

Requirements

Degree holder in Communications / Public Relations or equivalent;
At least 4 years of hands-on experience in public affairs, community relations, complaint handling, corporate communications and crisis management; 
Experience in releasing press materials and handling general public enquiries;
Proficiency in English and Chinese (both Cantonese and Putonghua);
Excellent interpersonal and communications skills;
Well versed in MS office applications (e.g. Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese word processing); and
Willing to work at construction site office.

We offer competitive package and attractive employee benefits including 5-day work / 5.5-day work (2 ex-gratia Sat-off per month), ex-gratia rest day, birthday holiday, All-in-One Flexible Benefit Plan, training sponsorship and discretionary bonus.

Application with full resume, current and expected salary, and available date should be sent through email to The Human Resources Manager, quoting the appropriate reference number via email to hr @chunwo.com write to 5C, Hong Kong Spinners Industrial Building, 601-603 Tai Nan West Street, Cheung Sha Wan, Kowloon, Hong Kong.  

For more information, please visit our website at www.chunwo.com.
Personal data provided by job applicants would be used for recruitment purposes only.

Job Descriptions:
To provide general clerical and administration support in construction site;
To handle and maintenance the attendance record of site staffs/Labourers;
Other general administration duties
Requirements:
Form 5 or above;
Above 3 years site admin experience;
Proficiency in PC applications including MS Office and Chinese Word Processing;
Willing to work at site office
We offer very attractive remuneration package and career advancement opportunities for the right candidates.  Interested parties please send a covering letter and detailed resume including current and expected salary to the Head of HR & Admin, 18/F., Tung Hip Commercial Building, 244-252, Des Voeux Road Central, Hong Kong or by email via "Apply Now"
Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and handled confidentially by authorized personnel for recruitment-related purposes only.

Responsibilities:

Provide clerical duties to the project team: typing, filing, register correspondence and report’s preparation;
Assist with ad-hoc duties when required;
Requirements:
F.5 or above;
Min. 3 years' relevant experience, preferably has experience in construction industry;
Proficiency in MS Office (Word, Excel & PowerPoint) and Chinese Word Processing;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Initiative and able to organize work efficiently and independently;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills; and
Immediate available is preferred.

For interested parties, please submit your application with detailed resume, current and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".

Applications will be treated in confidence and only be used for recruitment purposes. Those not being invited for interview within 3 months may consider their applications unsuccessful.
